				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, leave it to me to start us out... I'll bite.
<br />

<br />
Huh?
<br />

<br />
Hehe, Do I understand you correctly?
<br />

<br />
Are you saying that you will be singing 4 songs all the time during battle, but once in a while, you will be throwing in 2 other songs in place of two of your regular ones to give partial benefit during the fight?
<br />

<br />
If so, make sure you can afford to lose the two fighting songs you drop for those times.
<br />

<br />
If that's not what you're talking about, then I repeat... Huh?
<br />

<br />
Oh and I see your point about Nivs and Replenishment.  With my Kelin's Seven String Lute I can do 282 hp in 6 ticks at 56.  However, I wouldn't likely throw those in during combat unless the cleric was LOM and was using it for the mana regen.  47 hp a tick isn't going to save a tank getting doubled for 250+.
<br />

<br />
Not much of a discussion starter but it's the best I cold come up with. Maybe I'll re-read the first post a few more times and it will help.
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian
<br />

