			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: The Nature of the Twist<a name="5403"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 13 03 1:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>
<br />
Most songs are 18 secs long, or 3 ticks.
<br />

<br />
Most people will limit themselves to keeping 3-4 songs
<br />
up at all times.
<br />

<br />
However, it is possible to have 6-7 songs up at once,
<br />
tho some will fade before being able to refresh them.
<br />

<br />
What I'm saying is if you pick the 2-3 songs that will
<br />
fade to be the effect type songs, like heal and nivs,
<br />
you can do some serious twists :-D
<br />

<br />
although 50hp or so a tick isn't gonna save a tank getting
<br />
doubled, it will definitely add up over the course of a few
<br />
fights and you will notice your downtime significantly
<br />
decreasing.
<br />

<br />
The bard fight is a lot like chess, there's the opening, the 
<br />
mid-fight strategies, and end-fight songs.  I'd like to hear
<br />
what other bards use as combos for openers, mid-game,
<br />
and end-game, I'm sure we can all teach other something
<br />
new :-D
<br />

<br />
Astuce Subterfuge</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
