				<td colspan="2"><span>
<br />
Hehe, I hope they're not overlooking that aspect my friend
<br />
since &quot;skipping a beat&quot; is the whole point I was trying to 
<br />
make in the first post.
<br />

<br />
I do believe that your take on it might make it more easily
<br />
understandable.  Especially on the drawbacks vs. benefits.
<br />

<br />
I guess on my twists you could phrase it like this:
<br />

<br />
The overall benefit of 4 songs that are 80 % active and
<br />
2 extra song that are 40 % active is worth a lot more,
<br />
to me, than 3 songs that are up 100 % of the time.
<br />

<br />
Quick example; I am grouped with a shammy and a druid.
<br />
The shammy slowed the mob and the druid snared it.
<br />

<br />
Now, there are still other benefits from the snare/slow song,
<br />
since it greatly reduces the targets agi and ac, esp when
<br />
amped/epic'ed/voice'd.  Since it really won't matter too much
<br />
if if the song is inactive at some parts of the fight, it is &quot;ok&quot;
<br />
to let this one fade.  However, pulsing it once will get you
<br />
about 18 secs of easier melee damage.  To me, it's a justified
<br />
benefit to throw in it once in a while during the fight, without
<br />
actually worrying about keeping it up at all times.  To me,
<br />
it is worth losing mebbe a second or less of haste/overhaste/
<br />
whateverelse I may be doing at the time.
<br />

<br />
some more thoughts,
<br />

<br />
Astuce Subterfuge</span></td>
