				<td colspan="2"><span>I agree that small gaps in coverage are for the most part insignificant. I normaly group with an enchater or shammy so in normal situationes I open with lvl 60 slow, duration 1 min  so play it and forget it.then I fall into my standard twist:
<br />

<br />
Cantata of Replenishment
<br />
Rhondo's for str/atk buff and ds
<br />
Psalm of choice for ds
<br />
Warsong of Vah Shir for overhaste
<br />

<br />
Near the end of the fight I'll drop Psalm for a snare if the mob is a runner and once he turns I'll drop Rhondo's to ensure full coverage of the snare. 
<br />

<br />
The first 3 are 12 sec duration and I get a few gaps depending on lag.
<br />
If Cantata drops momentarily its no biggie as its usually up again before the next regen tic.
<br />
A momentary drop in the ds is not going to make or break an encounter.
<br />
Only Warsong is important to keep up. The mellees will howl if it drops. Fortunately its duration is 18 secs so it never drops.
<br />

<br />
Also, the higher level Mezz songs are 18 sec duration so I can drop any one song and get complete coverage while doing CC.
<br />

<br />
As stated above, there are situations that demand full coverage. I drop to a 3 song twist at these times, sometimes 2 if the lag is really bad.
<br />

<br />
Amati
<br />
