			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: The Nature of the Twist<a name="5622"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 22 03 11:37 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ramblings of a tired Bard...
<br />

<br />
On the macro twisting... I tried this (setting up 2 or 3 songs on one key using /stopsong) but dumped it due to being locked into it.
<br />
The hard part of a macro like that is if you get a missed note you're stuck in the macro (unless you manually start the song). I stay with the single macro per key, and have 3 banks set up for different situations / songs.
<br />
I use a /pause of 4 which serves me well. On rare occasions / laggy areas I will still manually twist, and can keep 4 or 5 up about 95% of the time. 
<br />
Seems the time for /stopsong and cast refresh of the macro is much longer than doing it manually. Also allows you to choose which song you need right now. I'd hate to be stuck in a 30 or 40 sec macro and need to mez. But, to each his own.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
I have been &quot;skipping&quot; for most of my &quot;life&quot;. I pay major homage to Reed Stormwind for his time and effort on his spreadsheet. I wouldn't be the Bard I am today with out it.
<br />
If you haven't used it, get it. The info about every song is invaluable, especially since there are times when I even pull out the lil ole level 1 CoB. Rare, but it has served well.
<br />

<br />
One point I don't see too many times ~ you just need to get it started. Watch for the &quot;start message&quot;, or better yet position the cast window where it's easily visible. 
<br />
I have a UI mod where the cast bar is right under the mob name, but only shows when casting. Helps for timing when making macros. Soon as it ends on one cast, start another.
<br />
That will save you about 2 or 3 secs (or a whole other song!). Using this method, I can manually keep 5 songs up, and sometimes 6 or 7 with the longer lasting ones (Amp, Vah Shir, Assonance).
<br />

<br />
I seem to be lucky. While I don't have an uber PC (P2 450, 356 meg, Voodoo3 32 meg, DSL), I don't have too bad a lag issue (except raids / bazaar, but that's everyone hehe).
<br />
If you do have lag and can't upgrade equipment, find the &quot;tweaks&quot; ~~ turn off effects, grass, maybe even models and use single names ~~ all the litlle extras that you can live without. I do run with minimal effects and such, but can keep most of the models turned on. 
<br />
Oh, and if you're not fighting or on CC, auto-follow your MT and look down at 45 degrees. You can still see your general area (although just the boots / feet), but lag is mostly gone.
<br />

<br />
Main issue I see with part-time Bards (as I call em) is that they have likely played casters before and are in the frame of mind that the highest level spell is the best. For caster's that is mostly true. The next upgrade sends the lower one to the back of their book, only used during a &quot;newbie buff station&quot;, or never. 
<br />
Not to offend, but I feel this is why Bards get a bad rep in groups. The &quot;Bards can't do anything good&quot; or &quot;Jack of all, master of none&quot; type of posts / remarks are due to this.
<br />

<br />
We as Bards need to keep up with what came before due to the different components of each song. And with 2 or 3 per level, that's a LOT.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  Yes, some get moved to the back of the book, but don't forget them. At some point it can be useful. Make sure you talk within your group, let them know you're slowing, snaring, hasting, buffing, debuffing, etc, etc. Be pleasant, jovial, even funny. Make it &quot;the best group I've been in&quot; for them. Helps to dispell the &quot;mana battery&quot; mystic we have.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps, or at least provokes thought.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
