				<td colspan="2"><span>One of the reasons I don't use macros is for the ability to improvise when necessary. Lately I have been twisting 4 to 5 songs on lag days, 3 to 4 on bad days and raids. I have noticed that as I get up in level most songs seem to last a little longer. Better equipment, etc. play a part in that, I believe. Or, at least, I would like to think so. 
<br />

<br />
Example: I was soloing in EW, playing Selo's, Chant of Flame, Chant of Disease. Exchanging chain for Selo's when I was down to 1 mob, etc. I noticed, that a perfect set, left me with about 2.5 seconds or so, for another song, more or less, depending my activity level at the time. Changing instruments for weapons, etc. 
<br />

<br />
This also takes into account no missed notes, etc.
<br />

<br />
Just another thought on this, but it could be doable under the right circumstances.
<br />

<br />
Karinya
